- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the algorithmic aspect of edge bundling in graph drawings. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents approximation algorithms for minimizing the number of bundled crossings. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the relationship between the bundled crossing number and the orientable genus of the graph. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with graph drawings. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a less likely category, but the paper does involve combinatorial and graph-theoretic concepts.
